div.div: In the late 19th century, the British Empire nobility reigns while its working class suffers at their hands. Sympathetic to their plight, William James Moriarty wants to topple it all. Frustrated by the systemic inequity, Moriarty strategizes to fix the entire nation. Not even consulting detective Sherlock Holmes can stand in his way. It's time for crime to revolutionize the world! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode received an early screening on September 21st, 2020. The regular TV broadcast started on October 11th, 2020.
Comedy, Horror, Slice of Life, Supernatural

She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)
Yuutousei no Ura no Kao: Jitsu wa Ura Aka Joshi Datta Tonari no Seki no Bishoujo to Houkago ni Futarikiri

Love is always troubling. You want to have the courage to tell someone how you feel. You want to know who he likes. You want someone to listen to your worries. You want someone to give you a push. I know how you feel, and it hurts. Because I had a past I couldn't forget. And because now I have the "power" to save them.... That's why I, Io Akashi, became an angel. "I've finally found you, the angel of Kuze High." The angel touched the girl's cheek, in order to correct Yuzuki Minato's abnormal tendency to fall in love. This is a slightly mysterious coming-of-age story where memory and love play out softly.
(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
